Daud Olatunji, Abeokuta The Ogun State Government has disclosed that over one million children between the ages of  six months and five years across the state will be supplemented with Vitamin A as part of its plan to  reduce  infant mortality rate in the state. The government disclosed that the present administration was focusing on how infant mortality rate would reduce to 50 per cent in 2020. The commissioner-designate in the Ministry of Health, Dr Tomi Coker, said this in Abeokuta during a press briefing to outline the activities lined up for the 2019/2020 maternal, new born and child health week. Copyright PUNCH.
